body.p:
You may want to display the chapters title on a separate page, with a background for example.
      In order to do this, a new page should be defined in your customization
      CSS:@page chapter-title-page {
  background-image: url("resources/title-bg.png");
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: 100% 100%;
  background-position: center;
}After that, you need to replace the default "chapter" page definition by the one
      created
      before:*[class ~= "topic/topic"][is-chapter] {
  page: chapter-title-page;
}Then, you need to set it back on the content following the
      title:*[class ~= "topic/topic"][is-chapter] > *[class ~= "topic/title"] ~ *:not([class ~= "topic/title"]) {
  page: chapter;
}Finally, you can customize the title color, size,
      etc.:*[class ~= "topic/topic"][is-chapter]:not([is-part]) > *[class ~= "topic/title"] {
  color: white;
  font-size: 32pt;
}
